Protesters opposing the construction of a $ 1.4 billion telescope on a mountain in Hawaii they consider to be sacred were arrested after blocking a road leading to the site .
Police arrested 12 protesters when they tried to block trucks heading to the peak of Mauna Kea where one of the world 's largest telescopes is being built .
Native Hawaiian groups do not oppose the Thirty Meter Telescope itself , they disagree with the location of the highest point in the state which is considered a home of deities .